  "text": "The Kafka inter-broker replication protocol is implemented across multiple modules and packages. The core replication mechanism centers on the ReplicaFetcherThread (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaFetcherThread.scala), which extends AbstractFetcherThread to fetch data from the leader broker. The ReplicaFetcherThread communicates with the leader via the LeaderEndPoint interface (server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/LeaderEndPoint.java) and its implementations LocalLeaderEndPoint and RemoteLeaderEndPoint. The LeaderEpochFileCache (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/epoch/LeaderEpochFileCache.java) manages the leader epoch information to ensure proper offset truncation and recovery. The Partition class (core/src/main/scala/kafka/cluster/Partition.scala) implements the ISR (in-sync replica) management with maybeExpandIsr and maybeShrinkIsr methods, which handle the dynamic adjustment of the in-sync replicas set based on replication progress. LogStartOffset tracking is managed through LogStartOffsetIncrementReason (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogStartOffsetIncrementReason.java) and integrated into the UnifiedLog (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/UnifiedLog.java) class. The Replica class (server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/replica/Replica.java) maintains per-replica state including fetch offsets and timestamps through its ReplicaState (server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/replica/ReplicaState.java), and provides updateFetchStateOrThrow to update follower fetch positions. The PartitionFetchState (server/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/PartitionFetchState.java) manages the fetch state for each partition. The ReplicaManager (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ReplicaManager.scala) orchestrates the overall replication process, coordinating between the network layer, log storage, and replica state. The FetchRequest and FetchResponse classes (clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/requests/) define the protocol messages for inter-broker communication. The LeaderAndIsr metadata (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/metadata/LeaderAndIsr.java) and BrokersToIsrs controller (metadata/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/controller/BrokersToIsrs.java) maintain the ISR state in the metadata layer. Log offset management is supported through LogOffsetMetadata (storage/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/storage/internals/log/LogOffsetMetadata.java), LogOffsetSnapshot, and related classes that track commit offsets and high watermark progression."
}

